<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>A druid telling melees what to do...Yeah right :)</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/ZASHEE.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  ZASHEE IXI`BANE<br>Level 65 Druid<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_1.gif" title="Service Cross"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_16.gif" title="Service Star Cluster"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><br>Raid Leader<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=ZASHEE"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">ZASHEE</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=15&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i> I went through and read most of the posts here, and I have noticed that mob placement has been touched on, yet not stressed to the point that it really should...<br><br><br> All those wndorful things you can do to push a mob add damage, but the downfall is, it can also rduce argo from the MA. Bash, slam, kick and knockback spells all have a use and a purpose in the game, to place the mob.<br><br> When on a raid, use them only to place a mob, not just to get max DPS. The bst technique I have seen so far is not to put the mob in the corner, yet to have it against a wall with plenty of room for rogues to get in behind and do max damage.<br><br> In example, the warrior meets the mob and while attacking, swivels around turning the mob. The assist is called when the mob is turned. At this point, all DPS are to be even on the side of the mob, at max range for DPS, pushing the mob only to the wall, keeping the back open(even if we do not have a rogue it will still help) If you want to get behind the mob, do not use kick, bash, slam or knockback spells, as every swing the warrior makes is part of the argo, they are not DPS. <br><br> A warrior is to always be nose to nose with the mob at all times, in the front of the mob, this will get max damage, max argo and max DPS for the warrior, anyone that gets closer than the warrior can take taunt easily with the amount of DPS being done. Since the MA is the target of most heals, you can see how this would be bad.<br><br> The next closest to the mob, yet slightly behind the MA, would be the SA, staying very close, yet not closer to than the MA unless the MA goes down.<br><br> As for the casters, being able to do mass amounts of damage in a spit second, then sitting down for any reason, can also move the mob from where it has been placed. If you have the wrong spells memmed, then use what you can, or dont do any damage untill you have the spells you want. An example of this, is the two largest DoT casters in the game, Shaman and Necro. Both of these classes have a lot of damage they can do in seconds, along with nukes and debuffing, that is the reason both of these classes were givin the ability to have mana while standing... Canniblize and the Lich line, is how they get mana back, if you sit after doing that much damage, the mob will be on you as if the warrior had never even been in the room.<br><br> I just had to add this in. I hope it helps in some way.<br clear=all></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
